Ford Motor Co praised President Reagan'snomination of Alan Greenspan as Federal Reserve Board chairman,saying the conservative economist has a "sound record to fillthe void of (Paul) Volker's departure."    The number two U.S. auto maker said in a statement thatVolker "took office...at the beginning of a critical time forthe auto industry" and had had "a very positive impact on theU.S. economy." Reuter&#3;